# How to create a Github repository

- STEP 1: Create a new Github Account or Sign in to one -> [Github login page](https://github.com/login)
- STEP 2: Create a new repository -> Click [here](https://github.com/new)

  <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/F-l-a/NXUpdateTracker/main/Guides/Repository/1.png">
---
- STEP 3: Insert the name of the repository, select `Public` and create the repository

  <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/F-l-a/NXUpdateTracker/main/Guides/Repository/2.png">
---
- STEP 4: Inside the `Code` tab, create a new file

  <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/F-l-a/NXUpdateTracker/main/Guides/Repository/3.png">
---
- STEP 5: Write the file name, insert your versions and commit the changes to save them -> you can `CTRL+C`-`CTRL+V` from [here](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/F-l-a/FlaSwitch/main/Versions.json). Be sure to copy from the `[` to the `]` (all the page), otherwise you will probably get an error

  <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/F-l-a/NXUpdateTracker/main/Guides/Repository/4.png">
---
- STEP 6: Confirm the commit

  <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/F-l-a/NXUpdateTracker/main/Guides/Repository/5.png">
---
- STEP 7: Redo STEP 5 and STEP 6, with [this](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/F-l-a/FlaSwitch/main/Visibility.json) file. File Name: `Visibility.json`

  <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/F-l-a/NXUpdateTracker/main/Guides/Repository/5.png">
---
- (STEP 8: Put the info (OWNER-REPO-FILE_PATH) inside the `/switch/NXUpdateTracker/githubInfo.ini` file. If you are following the [Usage Guide](https://github.com/F-l-a/NXUpdateTracker/wiki/Usage-Guide), this will be explained later)

  <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/F-l-a/NXUpdateTracker/main/Guides/Repository/6.png">
